<h1>Cheese Sauce</h1>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
  <li>1 1/2 C russet potatoes (about 1 medium), finely diced</li>
  <li>1/4 C red bell pepper, finely diced</li>
  <li>1/2 small yellow onion, diced</li>
  <li>2 T pine nuts</li>
  <li>2 T tahini</li>
  <li>1 T lemon juice</li>
  <li>2 T nutritional yeast</li>
  <li>2 T arrowroot powder</li>
  <li>1 t salt</li>
</ul>
<h2>Steps</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Combine the potato, bell pepper, onion, and pine nuts in a small saucepan and cover with water.</li>
  <li>Bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce heat to medium and cook until the potatoes are very tender, about 10 minutes.</li>
  <li>Drain, reserving 3/4 C of the cooking water.</li>
  <li>Combine the drained potato mixture, reserved cooking water, tahini, lemon juice, nutritional yeast, arrowroot powder, and salt in a high powered blender.</li>
  <li>Blend on high until everything is smooth and creamy, about 3 minutes (the starch in the potatoes needs to break down).</li>
</ol>
